.TH UPGRADE-KALI 1 "December 2025" "distup 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
upgrade-kali \- upgrade Kali Linux rolling or bleeding-edge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B upgrade-kali
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fBrolling\fR|\fBbleeding-edge\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B upgrade-kali
upgrades Kali Linux systems using the rolling or bleeding-edge repositories.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-V
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show help message.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B rolling
Standard Kali rolling release (recommended).
.TP
.B bleeding-edge
Add bleeding-edge repository with experimental packages.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apt/sources.list
Repository configuration (backed up before modification).
.TP
.I /var/log/upgrade-kali-*.log
Log file containing detailed upgrade output.
